Trade Odds — Canonical Dashboard Source (read-only reference)
=============================================================

This directory contains the SOURCE CODE of the Trade Odds dashboard that runs
on the home Mac mini. The thin client at /server.mjs proxies to it.

You normally DON'T need this. Just run `run.bat` / `run.sh` in the repo root
and the thin client serves the live dashboard from the Mac via Cloudflare
Tunnel — no setup, no API keys.

This source is pushed here for:
  1. Transparency — see exactly what the dashboard is doing
  2. Backup — versioned snapshot in git
  3. Standalone mode — run a fully-local copy (requires API keys + ClickHouse)

To run STANDALONE (advanced):
  - Need Node 20+
  - Need a .env with MASSIVE_API_KEY, UW_API_KEY, CLICKHOUSE_URL, etc.
  - Need the memory/ directory populated (idea_board.json, signals.json, etc.)
    — these are produced by clawd scanners on the Mac; you'd need to sync them
  - node source/dashboard.mjs   →  http://localhost:7071

Files:
  dashboard.mjs                       — main entry, single-file Node http server
  backfill_earnings_history.mjs       — pulls UW earnings into memory/uw_earnings_history.json
  lib/clickhouse.mjs                  — ClickHouse query helper
  lib/massive.mjs                     — Polygon API helper (lib/massive name is historical)
  lib/uw_api.mjs                      — UW REST client with rate limiter + disk cache
  lib/signals.mjs                     — signal-bus reader

The canonical instance is daemonized via launchd on the Mac mini:
  com.dalcosser.clawd-tile-dashboard
